  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-04-23",
    "date": "2020-05-02T20:42:19Z",
    "text": "Point-of-Care Testing Prize Competitions Act of 2020\n\nThis bill requires the National Institutes of Health (NIH), in consultation with the National Institutes of Standards and Technology (NIST), to conduct a prize competition for institutions of higher education in order to incentivize research on point-of-care testing that is capable of detecting current or past infection with COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) and meets other\u00a0specified criteria. The NIST must assist the NIH with the development of certain validation protocols and standards for the testing."
  },
